{"questionId":"9076153","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A beam of coherent monochromatic light from a distant galaxy is used in an optics experiment on Earth.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The air between the slits and the screen is replaced with water. The refractive index of water is 1.33.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the wavelength of the light in water.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{633.0}}{{1.33}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>633.0</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.33</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =&nbsp;476 <strong>«</strong>nm<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076153","referenceCode":"18M.2.SL.TZ1.b.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the wavelength of the light in water.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.4 – Wave behaviour","Core","Topic 4: Waves"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}